Here's how to implement all three in your `EditProductPage`:

**XAML — custom back button**
```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior
            TextOverride="Cancel"
            Command="{Binding NavigateBackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- your form here -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Code-behind / ViewModel — confirmation + cancel logic**
```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    public bool HasUnsavedChanges { get; set; }

    public ICommand NavigateBackCommand { get; }

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        NavigateBackCommand = new Command(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
        BindingContext = this;
    }

    // Intercepts the HARDWARE / swipe-gesture back button
    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        if (!HasUnsavedChanges)
            return base.OnBackButtonPressed();   // allow normal navigation

        // Fire-and-forget the async prompt; return true to CANCEL navigation for now
        Dispatcher.Dispatch(async () => await TryNavigateBack());
        return true;   // true = "I handled it, don't navigate"
    }

    private async Task TryNavigateBack()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!leave)
                return;           // user chose Stay → cancel navigation
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoBackAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| Mechanism | What it covers |
|---|---|
| `OnBackButtonPressed` | Android hardware back, desktop back |
| `Shell.BackButtonBehavior.Command` | Shell toolbar back button (replaces default) |
| `TextOverride="Cancel"` | Relabels the toolbar button |
| Return `true` from `OnBackButtonPressed` | Cancels navigation |

> **Caveat:** iOS swipe-back gesture bypasses both hooks. To fully block it, disable it with `Shell.PresentationMode` or set `IsEnabled="false"` on the `BackButtonBehavior` while changes are dirty, which removes the swipe gesture on iOS Shell pages.
